25/01/2004
BRUSSELS, Belgium -- The EU is pleased with early efforts by Croatia's new government, according to EU security chief Javier Solana, who met on Friday (23 January) with Croatian Foreign Minister Miomir Zuzul. Brussels has no doubt that Croatia will join the Union, said Solana, who added that in his view, the government is doing its best on war crimes co-operation. Zuzul said the country would boost efforts to join Euro-Atlantic structures. (Croatian Radio, BBC, HINA - 23/01/04)
